					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13304611#post-4643072</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13304611/scp-5987#post-4643072</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2020 04:43:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NatVoltaic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2800867</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This article is a reference with nothing else going for it. The initial concept is cool, but the rest never explores it to a deeper degree, instead stringing a series of plot developments together that amount to a lackluster ending. If anything it feels like the attempt to play off sirenhead stifles any creative direction this could have, only serving to railroad it to a moment of &quot;oh, <em>that's</em> the reference!&quot; beyond which I have no reason to care about anything I just read. If anything the attempt to explicitly hammer it in took me out of the experience, because it didn't make me feel like I was reading a story; it made me feel like I was reading an internet culture gag in the guise of a story.</p> <p>-1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
